    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are an experienced technical recruiter.\n\nYou will receive:\n\n1. A candidate profile.\n2. A list of job titles.\n\nFor each job title, evaluate how well it matches the candidate based on:\n\n- Technical skills\n- Technologies used in projects\n- Preferred roles\n- Education\n- Fresher suitability\n\nRules:\n\n- Compare the title with the candidate's skills and projects.\n- Consider closely related roles (e.g. Backend Developer ↔ FastAPI Developer, AI Engineer ↔ GenAI Engineer).\n- Personal projects count as relevant experience for fresher roles.\n- Be realistic. Do not inflate scores.\n- Every input job must appear exactly once in the output.\n\nReturn the result using the required output format.\n\nOutput Rules:\n\n- Return every input job exactly once.\n- Copy uniqueId exactly as provided.\n- Copy title exactly as provided.\n- atsScore must be a number between 0 and 100.\n- Do not include any other fields.\n- Do not rename any field.\n\nCandidate:\n\n{{ JSON.stringify($json.resume, null, 2) }}\n\nJobs:\n\n{{ JSON.stringify($json.jobs, null, 2) }}",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3.1,
      "position": [
